                <text type="synoptic_situation">A weak trough skims the southeastern waters later today and into Wednesday morning, as a high pressure system moves across waters to the south on Wednesday. The high is forecast to be centred over Tasmania on Thursday, as it continues to extend a ridge over SA on Friday.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
